# Only needed when the API is served from a different origin than this
# client (e.g. a separate api-allstar.example.com subdomain, rather
# than a reverse proxy putting both behind one origin). Baked into the
# built bundle at `vite build` time -- changing it means rebuilding,
# not just restarting. Leave unset for a same-origin deployment (every
# /api and SSE URL then resolves relative to wherever this app itself
# is served, which is also what makes the dev-mode proxy in
# vite.config.ts work).
#
# Must exactly match the value the server's own CLIENT_ORIGIN is set
# to allow (see server/.env.example), no trailing slash.
#VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api-allstar.example.com
